<TITLE> Asif seeks board help in fighting doping case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KARACHI, Nov 11 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Suspended Pakistan pace bowler Mohammad Asif has asked the Pakistan Cricket Board to support him in a legal battle against a doping ban after he tested positive for the steroid nandrolone. "The previous board didn't help me out at all in this doping offence. I have been fighting a lone battle," Asif told Reuters on Monday. The PCB suspended Asif from all cricket in August after he tested positive in a dope test carried out during the semi-final of the Indian Premier League (IPL) in June. The IPL drugs inquiry tribunal, which is hearing Asif's appeal, is due to meet in Mumbai on Nov. 20
